Business Brief -- Pricor Inc.:
   Decision on Jails to Result
   In Restatement of Net Loss
The charge prompted the Murfreesboro, Tenn., company to
restate its results for the third quarter and nine months
ended Dec. 31. For the quarter, the company is now reporting
a net loss of $818,000, or 13 cents a share, compared with a
net loss of $389,000, or six cents a share, originally. For
the nine months, the company is now reporting a net loss of
$1,375,000, or 22 cents a share, compared with a net loss of
$946,000, or 15 cents a share, originally.
   Pricor operates and manages special-education schools,
treatment centers and correctional facilities in a half-dozen
states.